Statements: each of these drugs inhibited the serum stimulated phosphorylation of known raf and mtor substrates .
rapamycin inhibited the fgf-2 induced proliferation of two different small cell lung cancer lines ( sclc ) , whereas pd098059 inhibited one and not the other [ xref_bibr ] .

we also observed unexpected rapamycin inhibition of the phosphorylation of erk , as well as bay43-9006 inhibition of the phosphorylation of mtor substrates , p70s6k and 4ebp1 . ++++ combination treatment of a 10 nm dose of rapamycin plus a 10 nm dose of bay 43-9006 reduced the phosphorylation of erk to a level even below that seen in cells grown in the absence of serum . ++++ this inhibition of erk phosphorylation by combination of rapamycin and bay43-9006 was as effective as inhibition of mek by the u0126 compound .
rapamycin is an inhibitor of mtor kinase and reduces phosphorylation of its substrates , p70s6k and 4ebp1 [ xref_bibr ] .
in proximal tubular epithelial cells , insulin activated phosphorylation of 4ebp1 could be inhibited by pd098059 , suggesting a requirement for mapk [ xref_bibr ] .
this result showed that mek and erk activities contribute to phosphorylation of p70s6k and 4ebp1 .
